{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6be-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1701"},"text":"§ 1701.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional declaration of policy","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6bf-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Congress declares that it is the policy of the United States that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6c0-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the public lands be retained in Federal ownership, unless as a result of the land use planning procedure provided for in this Act, it is determined that disposal of a particular parcel will serve the national interest;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6c1-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the national interest will be best realized if the public lands and their resources are periodically and systematically inventoried and their present and future use is projected through a land use planning process coordinated with other Federal and State planning efforts;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6c2-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" public lands not previously designated for any specific use and all existing classifications of public lands that were effected by executive action or statute before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"October 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", be reviewed in accordance with the provisions of this Act;"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6c3-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Congress exercise its constitutional authority to withdraw or otherwise designate or dedicate Federal lands for specified purposes and that Congress delineate the extent to which the Executive may withdraw lands without legislative action;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6c4-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" in administering public land statutes and exercising discretionary authority granted by them, the Secretary be required to establish comprehensive rules and regulations after considering the views of the general public; and to structure adjudication procedures to assure adequate third party participation, objective administrative review of initial decisions, and expeditious decisionmaking;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6c5-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" judicial review of public land adjudication decisions be provided by law;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6c6-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" goals and objectives be established by law as guidelines for public land use planning, and that management be on the basis of multiple use and sustained yield unless otherwise specified by law;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6c7-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the public lands be managed in a manner that will protect the quality of scientific, scenic, historical, ecological, environmental, air and atmospheric, water resource, and archeological values; that, where appropriate, will preserve and protect certain public lands in their natural condition; that will provide food and habitat for fish and wildlife and domestic animals; and that will provide for outdoor recreation and human occupancy and use;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6c8-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9"},"text":"(9)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the United States receive fair market value of the use of the public lands and their resources unless otherwise provided for by statute;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6c9-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/10"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10"},"text":"(10)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" uniform procedures for any disposal of public land, acquisition of non-Federal land for public purposes, and the exchange of such lands be established by statute, requiring each disposal, acquisition, and exchange to be consistent with the prescribed mission of the department or agency involved, and reserving to the Congress review of disposals in excess of a specified acreage;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6ca-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/11"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"11"},"text":"(11)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" regulations and plans for the protection of public land areas of critical environmental concern be promptly developed;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6cb-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/12"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12"},"text":"(12)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the public lands be managed in a manner which recognizes the Nation’s need for domestic sources of minerals, food, timber, and fiber from the public lands including implementation of the Mining and Minerals Policy Act of 1970 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/1876"},"text":"84 Stat. 1876","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s21a"},"text":"30 U.S.C. 21a","children":[],"tail":") as it pertains to the public lands; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6cc-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/a/13"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"13"},"text":"(13)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Federal Government should, on a basis equitable to both the Federal and local taxpayer, provide for payments to compensate States and local governments for burdens created as a result of the immunity of Federal lands from State and local taxation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6cd-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s1701/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The policies of this Act shall become effective only as specific statutory authority for their implementation is enacted by this Act or by subsequent legislation and shall then be construed as supplemental to and not in derogation of the purposes for which public lands are administered under other provisions of law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idca68a6ce-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/579/tI/s102"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–579, title I, § 102","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2744"},"text":"90 Stat. 2744","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idca68a6cf-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idca68a6d0-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idca68a6d1-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This Act, referred to in subsecs. (a)(1), (3) and (b), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/579"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–579","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2743"},"text":"90 Stat. 2743","children":[],"tail":", known as the Federal Land Policy and Management Act of 1976. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Mining and Minerals Policy Act of 1970, referred to in subsec. (a)(12), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/631"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–631","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/1876"},"text":"84 Stat. 1876","children":[],"tail":", which is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s21a"},"text":"section 21a of Title 30","children":[],"tail":", Mineral Lands and Mining."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idca68a6d2-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"idca68a6d3-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2018 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/141/dO/s101/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–141, div. O, § 101(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-03-23"},"text":"Mar. 23, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/1059"},"text":"132 Stat. 1059","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/6/s7/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–6, § 7(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-02-15"},"text":"Feb. 15, 2019","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/133/15"},"text":"133 Stat. 15","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/116/6/s7/2"},"text":"“This division [see Tables for classification] may be cited as the ‘Stephen Sepp Wildfire Suppression Funding and Forest Management Activities Act’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"idca68a6d4-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2009 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/88/dA/tV/s501"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–88, div. A, title V, § 501","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/2968"},"text":"123 Stat. 2968","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/111/88/dA/tV/s501"},"text":"“This title [enacting sections 1748a and 1748b of this title] may be cited as the ‘Federal Land Assistance, Management, and Enhancement Act of 2009’ or ‘FLAME Act of 2009’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"idca68a6d5-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 1988 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/409/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–409, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-08-20"},"text":"Aug. 20, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/1086"},"text":"102 Stat. 1086","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/100/409/s1"},"text":"“This Act [enacting ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1723"},"text":"section 1723 of this title","children":[],"tail":", amending "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1716"},"text":"section 1716 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and sections 505a, 505b, and 521b of Title 16, Conservation, and enacting provisions set out as notes under sections 751 and 1716 of this title] may be cited as the ‘Federal Land Exchange Facilitation Act of 1988’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"idca68a6d6-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/579/tI/s101"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–579, title I, § 101","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2744"},"text":"90 Stat. 2744","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/94/579/tI/s101"},"text":"“This Act [see Tables for classification] may be cited as the ‘Federal Land Policy and Management Act of 1976’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"savings","id":"idca68a6d7-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Savings Provision","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/579/tVII/s701"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–579, title VII, § 701","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2786"},"text":"90 Stat. 2786","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/94/579/tVII/s701"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Nothing in this Act, or in any amendment made by this Act [see Short Title note above], shall be construed as terminating any valid lease, permit, patent, right-of-way, or other land use right or authorization existing on the date of approval of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":"]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"“(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Notwithstanding any provision of this Act, in the event of conflict with or inconsistency between this Act and the Acts of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1937-08-28"},"text":"August 28, 1937","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/50/874"},"text":"50 Stat. 874","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1181a–118"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 1181a–118","children":[],"tail":"1j [now "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s2601"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 2601","children":[],"tail":" et seq., see Tables for classification]), and "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1939-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1939","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/753"},"text":"53 Stat. 753","children":[],"tail":"), insofar as they relate to management of timber resources, and disposition of revenues from lands and resources, the latter Acts shall prevail."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"“(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" All withdrawals, reservations, classifications, and designations in effect as of the date of approval of this Act shall remain in full force and effect until modified under the provisions of this Act or other applicable law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"“(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Nothing in this Act, or in any amendments made by this Act, shall be construed as permitting any person to place, or allow to be placed, spent oil shale, overburden, or byproducts from the recovery of other minerals found with oil shale, on any Federal land other than Federal land which has been leased for the recovery of shale oil under the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1920-02-25"},"text":"February 25, 1920","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/41/437"},"text":"41 Stat. 437","children":[],"tail":", as amended; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s181"},"text":"30 U.S.C. 181","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"“(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Nothing in this Act shall be construed as modifying, revoking, or changing any provision of the Alaska Native Claims Settlement Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/85/688"},"text":"85 Stat. 688","children":[],"tail":", as amended; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1601"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 1601","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"“(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Nothing in this Act shall be deemed to repeal any existing law by implication.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"“(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Nothing in this Act shall be construed as limiting or restricting the power and authority of the United States or—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" as affecting in any way any law governing appropriation or use of, or Federal right to, water on public lands;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" as expanding or diminishing Federal or State jurisdiction, responsibility, interests, or rights in water resources development or control;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"“(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" as displacing, superseding, limiting, or modifying any interstate compact or the jurisdiction or responsibility of any legally established joint or common agency of two or more States or of two or more States and the Federal Government;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"“(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" as superseding, modifying, or repealing, except as specifically set forth in this Act, existing laws applicable to the various Federal agencies which are authorized to develop or participate in the development of water resources or to exercise licensing or regulatory functions in relation thereto;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"“(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" as modifying the terms of any interstate compact;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"“(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" as a limitation upon any State criminal statute or upon the police power of the respective States, or as derogating the authority of a local police officer in the performance of his duties, or as depriving any State or political subdivision thereof of any right it may have to exercise civil and criminal jurisdiction on the national resource lands; or as amending, limiting, or infringing the existing laws providing grants of lands to the States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"h"},"text":"“(h)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" All actions by the Secretary concerned under this Act shall be subject to valid existing rights.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"“(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The adequacy of reports required by this Act to be submitted to the Congress or its committees shall not be subject to judicial review.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"j"},"text":"“(j)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Nothing in this Act shall be construed as affecting the distribution of livestock grazing revenues to local governments under the Granger-Thye Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/85"},"text":"64 Stat. 85","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s580h"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 580h","children":[],"tail":"), under the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1908-05-23"},"text":"May 23, 1908","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/35/260"},"text":"35 Stat. 260","children":[],"tail":", as amended; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s500"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 500","children":[],"tail":"), under the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1913-03-04"},"text":"March 4, 1913","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/37/843"},"text":"37 Stat. 843","children":[],"tail":", as amended; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s501"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 501","children":[],"tail":"), and under the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1910-06-20"},"text":"June 20, 1910","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/557"},"text":"36 Stat. 557","children":[],"tail":").”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"separability","id":"idca68a6d8-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Severability","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/579/tVII/s707"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–579, title VII, § 707","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2794"},"text":"90 Stat. 2794","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/94/579/tVII/s707"},"text":"“If any provision of this Act [see Short Title note set out above] or the application thereof is held invalid, the remainder of the Act and the application thereof shall not be affected thereby.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idca68a6d9-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Timber Sales and Long-Term Contracting for the Bureau of Land Management","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/119/21/tV/s50301/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 119–21, title V, § 50301(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-07-04"},"text":"July 4, 2025","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/139/147"},"text":"139 Stat. 147","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/119/21/tV/s50301/b"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Definitions","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this subsection:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"“(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Public lands","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term ‘public lands’ has the meaning given the term in section 103 of the Federal Land Policy and Management Act of 1976 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1702"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 1702","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Resource management plan","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term ‘resource management plan’ means a land use plan prepared for public lands under section 202 of the Federal Land Policy and Management Act of 1976 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1712"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 1712","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"“(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Secretary","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The term ‘Secretary’ means the Secretary of the Interior, acting through the Director of the Bureau of Land Management.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Timber sales on public lands.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"“(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In general","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"For each of fiscal years 2026 through 2034, the Secretary shall sell timber annually on public lands in a total quantity that is not less than 20,000,000 board-feet greater than the quantity of board-feet sold in the previous fiscal year.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Limitation","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The timber sales under subparagraph (A) shall be subject to the applicable resource management plan in effect on the date of enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2025-07-04"},"text":"July 4, 2025","children":[],"tail":"]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"“(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Long-term contracting for the bureau of land management.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"“(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Long-term contracting","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"For the period of fiscal years 2025 through 2034, the Secretary shall enter into not fewer than 5 long-term contracts with private persons or other public or private entities under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-07-31/s1"},"text":"section 1 of the Act of July 31, 1947","children":[],"tail":" (commonly known as the ‘Materials Act of 1947’) ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/681"},"text":"61 Stat. 681","children":[],"tail":", chapter 406; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s601"},"text":"30 U.S.C. 601","children":[],"tail":"), for the disposal of vegetative materials described in that section on public lands."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Contract length","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The period of a contract entered into to meet the requirement under subparagraph (A) shall be not less than 20 years, with options for extensions or renewals, as determined by the Secretary.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"“(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Receipts","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Any monies derived from a contract entered into to meet the requirements under subparagraphs (A) and (B) shall be deposited in the general fund of the Treasury.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idca68a6da-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References to Division O of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/141"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–141","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/141/dO/s101/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–141, div. O, § 101(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-03-23"},"text":"Mar. 23, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/1059"},"text":"132 Stat. 1059","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/6/s7/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–6, § 7(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-02-15"},"text":"Feb. 15, 2019","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/133/15"},"text":"133 Stat. 15","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/116/6/s7/2"},"text":"“A reference to the Wildfire Suppression Funding and Forest Management Activities Act [div. O of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/141"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–141","children":[],"tail":", see Short Title of 2018 Amendment note above], including a reference in a regulation, order, or other law, is deemed to refer to the Stephen Sepp Wildfire Suppression Funding and Forest Management Activities Act.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idca68a6db-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Existing Rights-of-Way","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/579/tVII/s706/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–579, title VII, § 706(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2794"},"text":"90 Stat. 2794","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/94/579/tVII/s706/b"},"text":"“Nothing in section 706(a) [see Tables for classification], except as it pertains to rights-of-way, may be construed as affecting the authority of the Secretary of Agriculture under the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1897-06-04"},"text":"June 4, 1897","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/30/35"},"text":"30 Stat. 35","children":[],"tail":", as amended, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s551"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 551","children":[],"tail":"); the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1937-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 1937","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/50/525"},"text":"50 Stat. 525","children":[],"tail":", as amended, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s1010–121"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 1010–121","children":[],"tail":"2); or the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-09-03"},"text":"September 3, 1954","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/1146"},"text":"68 Stat. 1146","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s931c"},"text":"43 U.S.C. 931c","children":[],"tail":").”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
